18/11/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Former Bosnian Serb political leader Radovan Karadzic, who tops the UN tribunal's list of most wanted war crimes indictees, was spotted at a former army headquarters in Republika Srpska last June, according to a Bosnian Serb government report.
It said the fugitive managed to escape before the arrival of foreign troops.
(Scotsman - 18/11/05)
